content:
The Service Analytics template gets you started fast with Analytics and provides a clear path through your Service Cloud data on any device. Whether you’re a service manager or agent, you get everything you need in one place to uncover key data insights to help you grow your business.

The Service Analytics app includes prebuilt dashboards and datasets to accelerate data exploration for both service managers and agents.

Set up your organization to use the Service Analytics by enabling CRM Analytics and creating and assigning permission sets.

Follow these steps to create Service Analytics and start uncovering the value of your Salesforce data—fast.

Create Service Analytics with the configuration wizard so the app reflects how your company prefers to view Service Cloud data.

Members of your team can only use Service Analytics if you share it with them.

To restore deleted or altered dashboards or change wizard settings, reconfigure an existing version of Service Analytics.

Delete apps to start app creation all over or to get rid of apps you no longer use.

Take advantage of the latest Service Analytics features by upgrading your app every time we release a new version.

Schedule a daily app refresh to assure that Service Analytics uses up-to-date data.

Add Service Analytics dashboards to Salesforce pages so your service team can get a complete view of their cases and take appropriate action.

Service Analytics requires that Service Cloud include specific data, initially supports a limited set of Salesforce objects, and has other miscellaneous limitations.
title: Getting Started with Service Analytics
